There's one line that
runs through the county.

04:15.256 --> 04:17.867
All right.
Anything else?

04:19.673 --> 04:21.245
We drove for a while.

04:21.519 --> 04:22.912
I counted.

04:23.824 --> 04:25.830
I got almost to 700.

04:25.954 --> 04:27.099
That's a little
over 10 minutes.

04:27.191 --> 04:28.859
Lots of turns. I...

04:32.241 --> 04:34.017
I tried to keep track.

04:35.513 --> 04:36.732
I couldn't.

04:36.852 --> 04:39.871
It's okay.
You're doing great.

04:40.632 --> 04:41.998
Anything else?

04:43.071 --> 04:44.665
At the end,

04:44.763 --> 04:46.676
we turned on to a dirt road.

04:46.782 --> 04:52.016
I could hear gravel or rocks.

04:52.119 --> 04:55.695
We drove for maybe 5 minutes.

04:56.244 --> 04:57.940
Then we stopped.

04:58.062 --> 04:59.807
They opened the trunk.

04:59.932 --> 05:01.117
And what did you see?

05:01.230 --> 05:02.309
Woods.

05:02.418 --> 05:04.888
It was dark.
I couldn't see much.

05:05.035 --> 05:06.401
Two men,

05:07.078 --> 05:09.888
one blond, one dark hair.

05:12.240 --> 05:14.715
They put me inside here.

05:14.856 --> 05:16.680
I could hear their shovels,

05:17.217 --> 05:18.613
then the dirt.

05:21.681 --> 05:24.232
That's all I can remember.

05:25.011 --> 05:27.733
Hey. You did good,
Debra.

05:30.155 --> 05:31.869
We are gonna find you.

05:32.826 --> 05:34.533
Deidre's gonna stay with you.

05:35.855 --> 05:38.061
Debra, I'm here. I'm gonna stay
on the line with you, okay?

05:38.174 --> 05:40.097
There's 8 different railroad
crossings in Milton County.

05:40.212 --> 05:41.432
Okay, but she's to the east,

05:41.532 --> 05:42.732
Cedarville State forest.

05:42.860 --> 05:44.500
It's 3,000 acres.
There's 12 access roads,

05:44.598 --> 05:45.333
they're all gravel.

05:45.444 --> 05:46.443
It's way too much
ground to cover.

05:46.538 --> 05:47.428
How much time do we have?

05:47.553 --> 05:49.622
They abducted her,
traveled by car.

05:49.792 --> 05:51.490
It takes time to bury someone.

05:51.970 --> 05:53.188
How much air do you
think she has?

05:53.290 --> 05:55.904
3-5 hours maybe.

05:57.308 --> 05:58.076
We got to find her.

05:58.192 --> 05:59.068
Police found Alex's car

05:59.163 --> 06:01.329
out on Route 4 near Cedarville.
We're gonna check it out.

06:57.306 --> 06:58.718
Morning, Claire.

06:59.806 --> 07:02.700
Whatever it is
you're considering doing,

07:03.605 --> 07:04.880
don't.

07:06.033 --> 07:07.254
Now come on.

07:08.926 --> 07:10.158
Back inside.

07:29.374 --> 07:31.353
So this is your
ending, a lighthouse?

07:32.704 --> 07:34.998
You don't find that the
least bit predictable?

07:35.634 --> 07:38.367
I... I find it fitting.

07:38.494 --> 07:41.861
- Or predictable.
- It's a motif, Claire.

07:42.036 --> 07:43.229
It bookends the story.

07:43.342 --> 07:44.289
Yeah. You're a brilliant
teacher, Joe,

07:44.416 --> 07:45.866
but it never really
translated to your writing.

07:45.969 --> 07:47.412
- Don't you--
- What? You're gonna kill me?

07:47.529 --> 07:50.058
You're gonna do it anyway.
You might as well just get it over with.

07:54.567 --> 07:55.737
Not just yet, no.

07:55.863 --> 07:57.327
Oh, right.

07:57.454 --> 07:58.983
We're waiting for Ryan.

07:59.074 --> 08:00.284
Yes, we are.

08:00.682 --> 08:03.700
Well, he-- he must
bear witness.

08:03.832 --> 08:07.622
Ryan has-- he has proved
remarkably resilient,

08:07.767 --> 08:11.169
but-- but I do believe
that your death will be the one

08:11.285 --> 08:14.207
that finally does
him in. Heh.

08:14.707 --> 08:16.363
Like I said...

08:17.077 --> 08:18.740
predictable.

08:19.127 --> 08:21.781
You know, you're not being
terribly good company, Claire.

08:21.875 --> 08:24.249
No. I'm finding your
temperament most, um...

08:24.665 --> 08:26.801
most provoking.

08:27.584 --> 08:30.187
In-- in fact, I think I've had
enough of you for the moment.

08:30.280 --> 08:31.495
Come here. Come on.

08:34.547 --> 08:35.496
Unh.

08:36.397 --> 08:37.763
Joe?

08:38.058 --> 08:39.169
Joe!

08:42.611 --> 08:43.703
Aah!

08:56.976 --> 08:58.271
This is definitely the car.

08:58.382 --> 08:59.650
Why leave it behind?

08:59.779 --> 09:02.534
Flat tire. Assuming
after they buried her.

09:02.870 --> 09:03.939
They could be anywhere.

09:04.034 --> 09:06.896
Okay, folks. We need a perimeter
search of the entire area. Let's go!

09:07.005 --> 09:08.493
Mike, check it out.

09:08.685 --> 09:10.041
Tire wall puncture.

09:10.134 --> 09:11.401
Somebody knifed it.

09:12.730 --> 09:14.989
They wanted us
to find this car.

09:25.358 --> 09:26.722
Unh!

09:34.932 --> 09:36.361
All right.

09:37.452 --> 09:39.194
- Give me some cover.
- Wait. What are you gonna do?

09:39.320 --> 09:40.388
Cover!

09:57.129 --> 09:58.415
Drop it!

09:58.895 --> 10:00.011
Drop the weapon.

10:02.405 --> 10:04.418
Where is Agent Parker?

10:05.186 --> 10:06.847
I don't know what
you're talking about.

10:06.988 --> 10:08.353
Hardy!

10:09.303 --> 10:10.198
Cuff him.

10:10.287 --> 10:11.625
Get on your knees!

10:16.807 --> 10:18.151
Put him in our car.

10:20.070 --> 10:21.981
Taking him back
to town for questioning?

10:23.005 --> 10:24.883
Yeah. We got him.

10:27.750 --> 10:29.726
Do what you need to do.

10:31.510 --> 10:33.899
- Who are you?
- My name is Neil Meyer.

10:34.669 --> 10:35.777
How did you end up here?

10:35.888 --> 10:39.598
Couple of kids hired me to
bring a boat up from Newport.

10:40.502 --> 10:41.439
What happened to your leg?

10:41.556 --> 10:42.886
It's my ankle.

10:43.823 --> 10:47.155
I think they broke it
so I couldn't run.

10:47.252 --> 10:48.744
What the hell is going on here?

10:48.829 --> 10:50.477
Who are these people?

10:50.643 --> 10:52.129
It's Joe Carroll.

10:54.928 --> 10:58.244
He's gonna kill us, isn't he?

11:18.421 --> 11:19.755
Where are we?

11:19.840 --> 11:22.505
Just a nice quiet place
where we can talk.

11:25.125 --> 11:26.421
Yeah. I've met some
of your militia friends.

11:26.535 --> 11:28.307
They had this really cool
way of questioning me.

11:28.396 --> 11:29.599
Yeah. I heard
about that.

11:29.676 --> 11:31.237
- Yeah?
- Unh!

11:31.538 --> 11:34.264
Oh. Then you know
what's about to happen.

11:34.497 --> 11:35.894
Here's how it works.

11:36.399 --> 11:38.395
We ask you a question,
you answer truthfully,

11:38.504 --> 11:40.056
or we beat you to a pulp.

11:41.216 --> 11:43.115
Where's Agent Parker?

11:43.440 --> 11:44.461
We don't have time for this.

11:44.571 --> 11:45.665
You need to start talking.

11:45.745 --> 11:47.504
Or what? You're FBI.
You can't do--

11:50.296 --> 11:52.483
I'm sorry.
You were saying?

11:53.473 --> 11:55.550
Where is Agent Parker?

11:55.649 --> 11:57.910
Okay, okay, okay.
I'll tell you.

11:58.012 --> 12:00.609
She's in a coffin
in the ground.

12:02.900 --> 12:04.092
Where is she?
Where is she?!

12:04.270 --> 12:07.374
Go ahead. Kill me.
I'm not talking. Heh heh.

12:07.538 --> 12:08.983
We're not gonna kill you,

12:09.084 --> 12:11.866
but we are gonna get
really, really close.

12:12.297 --> 12:13.983
Aah! Aah!

12:14.204 --> 12:15.706
Aah!

12:16.399 --> 12:18.280
Where is she, huh?

12:20.301 --> 12:21.821
Last chance!
Where?

12:21.932 --> 12:23.270
Okay, okay, okay, okay.
I'll tell you.

12:23.373 --> 12:24.199
Route 32.

12:24.288 --> 12:25.209
Where on 32?

12:25.292 --> 12:27.179
Woods near Macon Street.

12:30.409 --> 12:32.672
Yeah. We got a location.

12:33.064 --> 12:33.837
Got it.

12:33.932 --> 12:36.167
Woods off Route 32,
Macon Street. Go.

12:36.262 --> 12:38.107
- Now, now!
- We're 45 minutes away.

12:38.710 --> 12:41.050
If you're lying,
I will kill you.

12:41.177 --> 12:42.372
Unh!

12:43.493 --> 12:45.244
Get up. Get up!

12:55.898 --> 12:57.672
This won't budge.

12:58.551 --> 12:59.470
Hey. You should sit.

12:59.619 --> 13:01.261
No, no. See, we need to
get you out of here

13:01.398 --> 13:03.274
so you can go
for help, understand?

13:08.553 --> 13:09.997
Come with me.

13:11.759 --> 13:13.008
Where?

13:13.116 --> 13:15.451
In here.
I'm lonely.

13:15.532 --> 13:17.843
Joe, this man needs help.
You don't need him.

13:17.948 --> 13:18.885
You have me.

13:18.978 --> 13:20.568
Oh, do shut up.

13:20.674 --> 13:22.118
You're so bloody noble,

13:22.208 --> 13:23.964
always thinking of others.

13:30.283 --> 13:31.413
Sit down.

13:35.954 --> 13:38.202
Hands. Hands!

13:40.292 --> 13:41.965
What do you need that man for?

13:42.285 --> 13:43.995
You have your boat,
you have me.

13:46.872 --> 13:48.630
Oh. Perhaps
you're right.

13:51.488 --> 13:53.165
I suppose I should
finish him off.

13:53.919 --> 13:57.818
No. Joe, Joe,
you have to stop this!

13:58.202 --> 14:00.351
What if Ryan doesn't make it?

14:01.362 --> 14:05.086
Oh. I left him a-- a pretty
big trail of breadcrumbs

14:05.198 --> 14:08.437
to follow, so--
so I think--

14:08.545 --> 14:10.352
I think he'll make it in time.

14:10.459 --> 14:13.596
Anything to save
the love of his life.

14:17.596 --> 14:19.605
Do you remember, Claire,

14:20.498 --> 14:24.083
when we used to be in love?

14:27.333 --> 14:29.306
That love was a lie, Joe.

14:30.764 --> 14:34.603
W-we were really
good together.

14:47.051 --> 14:50.095
I'm really gonna
miss you, Claire.

14:54.567 --> 14:55.550
Look. My men
on their way,

14:55.666 --> 14:57.254
but they buried her
in the middle of nowhere.

14:57.365 --> 14:58.773
Turner, just hurry.

14:59.031 --> 15:00.007
How much longer?

15:00.733 --> 15:03.158
5 minutes, 10 at most.

15:06.617 --> 15:08.902
Debra, hold on
just one second, okay?

15:09.356 --> 15:11.169
Yes? Ryan!

15:11.657 --> 15:13.598
- How's she doing?
- I have her on the line.

15:14.429 --> 15:15.749
She's scared, Ryan.

15:17.124 --> 15:18.213
Put her on.

15:18.326 --> 15:20.211
Debra, Ryan's on.

15:21.539 --> 15:22.932
Debra?

15:25.826 --> 15:27.462
Debra?

15:29.239 --> 15:33.033
I'm here... Ryan.

15:33.146 --> 15:34.336
Mike's here with me, too.

15:34.443 --> 15:35.359
Hey. We know
where you are.

15:35.456 --> 15:37.087
We're on our way right now.

15:39.444 --> 15:40.987
Can you hear us?

15:41.354 --> 15:42.977
Yes.

15:43.173 --> 15:45.893
I need you to do me a favor.

15:46.804 --> 15:48.799
Call my sister.

15:48.897 --> 15:50.682
Hey. We're
on our way, okay?

15:50.785 --> 15:52.730
Tell her that I love her.

15:53.654 --> 15:57.370
My younger sister Beth.

15:58.128 --> 16:00.741
My parents, too.

16:01.719 --> 16:04.662
She'll know
how to contact them.

16:05.494 --> 16:11.318
We're not close, my family.

16:14.370 --> 16:17.252
That's my only regret.

16:17.399 --> 16:19.358
Deb, we're on our way,
okay, so stop talking.

16:19.468 --> 16:21.926
Just-- just save
your air, right?

16:22.785 --> 16:27.207
Mike... you're a good man.

16:30.116 --> 16:32.227
Don't lose that.

16:34.661 --> 16:36.714
Hey, Deb. Stop, okay?

16:36.822 --> 16:38.486
We're getting
really close, okay?

16:38.597 --> 16:40.020
We're almost there.

16:40.573 --> 16:42.425
And, Ryan,

16:42.779 --> 16:45.146
I chose this life...

16:47.617 --> 16:49.718
the FBI.

16:51.772 --> 16:54.087
I knew the deal,

16:54.193 --> 16:55.708
but this is not on you.

16:55.827 --> 16:58.296
You're g-- you're gonna make it.
You need to hold on.

16:58.637 --> 17:00.768
This is not on you.

17:00.880 --> 17:02.772
Don't you take it.

17:04.041 --> 17:07.064
I am not your fault.

17:09.267 --> 17:10.988
I knew the deal.

17:11.098 --> 17:13.756
Please just hold on.

17:25.875 --> 17:29.685
Please just hold on, Deb.

17:30.226 --> 17:31.871
Mike and I...

17:35.434 --> 17:37.226
We're gonna be there soon.

17:39.449 --> 17:41.258
I know.

18:01.551 --> 18:02.559
Get out!

18:03.522 --> 18:05.495
Where the hell is she?
Where is she?

18:05.608 --> 18:06.799
End of the path.

18:11.536 --> 18:12.855
Get down, get down.

18:19.097 --> 18:20.732
You better hurry.

18:22.667 --> 18:24.098
It's her!

18:24.518 --> 18:25.652
Debra!

18:25.749 --> 18:28.472
Debra! We're here!

18:28.698 --> 18:31.416
Hold on! Hold on!

18:32.269 --> 18:33.362
Hold on!

18:45.573 --> 18:47.901
Here. Get it by the sides right here.
Ready?

18:50.061 --> 18:51.763
1, 2!

18:53.085 --> 18:54.686
Oh, my God.
She's not breathing.

18:55.138 --> 18:56.474
Get her out, get her out.

19:51.373 --> 19:53.652
Aw. That's too bad.

19:53.908 --> 19:55.764
Just a little too late.

19:55.906 --> 19:57.158
Bummer.

20:09.529 --> 20:10.866
Ryan.

20:13.640 --> 20:14.648
Ryan, no!

20:34.555 --> 20:36.429
Come on.
Where are they?

20:56.190 --> 20:58.318
- What is that?
- It's Joe's book,

20:58.737 --> 21:00.079
left in the coffin.

