22:05.726 --> 22:06.798
Okay.

22:06.910 --> 22:09.449
Ryan, what is it?
What's next?

22:10.271 --> 22:11.318
It doesn't say.

22:11.436 --> 22:13.029
Of course it does.
Ryan!

22:14.301 --> 22:15.907
- Ryan.
- This is for me, alone.

22:16.021 --> 22:17.138
Ryan, you don't get
to do this by yourself.

22:17.237 --> 22:18.164
This is my fight, Mike.

22:18.266 --> 22:20.662
Hey. How can you
say that to me?

22:20.886 --> 22:22.406
You don't think this is
my fight, too?

22:22.505 --> 22:24.105
After what Joe's done,
this is my fight!

22:24.187 --> 22:25.005
He wants you dead.

22:25.099 --> 22:26.596
He wants everybody
close to me dead.

22:26.692 --> 22:28.685
- That was his plan.
- Yeah, but I'm not.

22:29.906 --> 22:31.217
Ryan, we can surprise him.

22:31.318 --> 22:32.269
I can't risk it.

22:32.357 --> 22:34.297
Hey, hey. Ryan,
you don't get to decide!

22:36.583 --> 22:37.806
Stay here.

22:39.111 --> 22:40.055
You're not gonna
shoot me, Ryan.

22:40.137 --> 22:42.029
- I'll shoot you in the leg.
- Ryan.

22:44.512 --> 22:45.824
Sorry, Mike.

22:47.360 --> 22:48.431
Ryan.

23:10.523 --> 23:13.680
When did you know, hmm?

23:14.505 --> 23:15.855
Know what?

23:16.159 --> 23:18.342
That I liked killing things,

23:19.944 --> 23:22.372
young girls and such, yeah?

23:23.516 --> 23:25.802
When did you know? I've always
wondered when you knew.

23:25.931 --> 23:27.575
When you were arrested.

23:27.725 --> 23:32.986
Yeah. You--
you suspected or you knew?

23:33.103 --> 23:36.666
When Ryan came to me,
he told me

23:36.810 --> 23:38.474
about the literary references.

23:40.258 --> 23:41.478
Unh.

23:44.660 --> 23:46.726
- You turned me in.
- No!

23:48.654 --> 23:50.888
He gave me the details
on the victims,

23:51.010 --> 23:54.074
and the saw the--
the symbolism.

23:54.193 --> 23:55.291
I sent him to you.

23:55.388 --> 23:56.850
Oh. Heh.

23:56.946 --> 23:58.128
Well, thanks for that.

23:58.226 --> 24:00.000
I was blinded when
it came to you, Joe.

24:00.105 --> 24:01.448
I...

24:01.927 --> 24:03.698
I loved you.

24:03.803 --> 24:04.780
You were my husband.

24:04.886 --> 24:09.106
Ryan, pitches up with his--
his cocksure swagger,

24:09.214 --> 24:11.946
and you finally face the truth.

24:13.581 --> 24:16.392
So you knew.

24:16.505 --> 24:18.861
- No. No, I didn't.
- Yes.

24:18.976 --> 24:20.376
No. I should have
seen it,

24:20.470 --> 24:21.471
but I didn't know,

24:21.572 --> 24:22.461
and because I didn't see it,

24:22.527 --> 24:23.508
all those girls died.

24:23.614 --> 24:25.542
I should have known,
I should have known

24:25.635 --> 24:26.400
what you were.

24:26.489 --> 24:27.934
Oh, I suppose you should have.

24:33.937 --> 24:35.651
I'm...

24:36.127 --> 24:38.438
I'm sorry. Claire.

24:39.595 --> 24:42.122
That was a horrible
thing to say.

24:42.417 --> 24:44.151
You mustn't blame yourself.

24:44.501 --> 24:47.476
Denial is a powerful thing.

24:48.388 --> 24:50.366
Yes. It runs
very deep,

24:50.477 --> 24:53.455
and it shields us from...

24:54.271 --> 24:56.873
from the worst truths.

24:56.976 --> 24:58.628
No, not me.

24:59.093 --> 25:00.611
I should have seen it.

25:00.714 --> 25:03.180
It was as if I killed
those girls myself.

25:03.290 --> 25:06.010
No. You certainly
did not.

25:06.946 --> 25:10.281
You are the victim
here, Claire.

25:10.639 --> 25:11.885
No.

25:12.280 --> 25:13.409
No.

25:13.599 --> 25:15.447
Ju-ju-just wait.

25:18.478 --> 25:19.321
Please let me go.

25:19.420 --> 25:21.203
- No. Come here.
- Joe.

25:21.344 --> 25:22.861
- I won't tell anyone.
- Shut up!

25:22.980 --> 25:24.215
What are you--
what are you doing?

25:24.902 --> 25:26.657
No talking.

25:27.026 --> 25:28.470
Please.

25:29.192 --> 25:31.338
Aah! Joe!

25:32.017 --> 25:33.332
Back up.

25:45.013 --> 25:48.511
That... Claire...

25:49.454 --> 25:52.838
is what it's like
to actually kill someone.

25:53.354 --> 25:55.749
Do you see the difference now?

25:55.896 --> 26:01.322
You killed no one, Claire,

26:01.473 --> 26:07.703
so don't you dare take
responsibility for my actions.

26:07.821 --> 26:11.542
I earned them, I own them.

26:11.819 --> 26:14.304
They are mine.

26:45.875 --> 26:46.906
_

26:51.726 --> 26:53.994
_

27:06.410 --> 27:08.183
Lose your gun and phone.

27:39.873 --> 27:41.401
Hello, Emma.

27:41.750 --> 27:45.234
Get on your knees,
hands on your head.

27:48.213 --> 27:50.535
Do you think I can't kill you?

27:51.312 --> 27:55.322
I have been instructed
to shoot you, Ryan.

27:56.739 --> 27:58.436
We're not playing
around anymore.

27:58.956 --> 28:00.373
This is it.

28:01.311 --> 28:03.319
If you want to see
Claire again,

28:03.582 --> 28:05.438
this is the only way.

28:06.263 --> 28:08.433
Just tell me where she is.

28:10.109 --> 28:11.294
Unh!

28:22.306 --> 28:24.436
Nice to see you again, Ryan.

28:44.850 --> 28:47.289
Oh, you're awake finally.

28:47.559 --> 28:49.854
Sit down. Sit down!

28:52.179 --> 28:53.978
Gonna need you to be

28:54.261 --> 28:56.858
a lot less combative.

28:56.970 --> 28:58.512
It's okay.

28:58.619 --> 28:59.993
It's gonna be okay.

29:00.090 --> 29:04.125
I knew you'd turn up.
Claire had her doubts.

29:04.955 --> 29:06.613
You found the book?

29:06.967 --> 29:07.892
Of course you
would have noticed

29:08.016 --> 29:10.185
the final chapter is missing.

29:10.300 --> 29:12.435
That's because
we are writing it now.

29:13.126 --> 29:14.224
You and I.

29:14.343 --> 29:16.714
How's it going to end,
Ryan, hmm?

29:16.799 --> 29:18.690
Does good triumph over evil?

29:18.842 --> 29:22.043
Does-- does the hero
rescue the girl?

29:22.148 --> 29:23.728
My hands are tied, Joe.

29:24.729 --> 29:26.625
Doesn't quite make
for a fair fight.

29:26.753 --> 29:30.912
Ryan, I have been stabbed
with both a knife and a fork,

29:31.015 --> 29:35.623
so I really don't think there's
gonna be any more fighting.

29:35.717 --> 29:38.207
Claire, you okay?

29:38.322 --> 29:40.399
Oh, she's fine. Yes.

29:40.512 --> 29:44.277
W-w-we've had a long
chat, Claire and I,

29:44.399 --> 29:45.987
about all sorts of things.

29:46.603 --> 29:51.052
You know, her guilt,
her suffering,

29:51.156 --> 29:54.780
her bad choice in men.

29:54.898 --> 29:56.806
You know, we damaged souls,

29:56.903 --> 30:00.763
we really do attract
one another, don't we?

30:01.573 --> 30:03.905
You're cursed
with a bad picker,

30:04.073 --> 30:05.376
you are.

30:05.553 --> 30:06.760
And let's face it,

30:06.867 --> 30:08.273
why would anyone fall in love

30:08.390 --> 30:09.766
with either of us

30:09.994 --> 30:13.093
total bloody disasters?

30:14.814 --> 30:18.193
We're so much alike.

30:18.303 --> 30:19.700
Your ending, Joe,

30:20.376 --> 30:22.012
tell me about it.

30:23.300 --> 30:25.096
What's my part, huh?

30:25.197 --> 30:26.718
What do I have to do?

30:27.348 --> 30:31.808
Well, you have
to be-- unh--

30:31.913 --> 30:35.302
you have to be
honest here, Ryan.

30:35.413 --> 30:37.424
- You got it.
- Right.

30:38.702 --> 30:42.457
So when did you fall
in love with my wife?

30:45.536 --> 30:48.232
- I don't know.
- Hmm.

30:49.582 --> 30:53.295
When you first met her, Ryan.

30:53.396 --> 30:54.645
Love at first sight.

30:54.734 --> 30:57.680
That's the acceptable answer.

30:57.786 --> 30:59.117
It starts as an attraction,

30:59.213 --> 31:01.242
but later, we're able
to look back on it

31:01.400 --> 31:06.779
and know that we always knew.

31:07.605 --> 31:11.468
Yes. It's much how I regard you
and I as a matter of fact,

31:11.567 --> 31:13.777
love at first sight.

31:15.208 --> 31:17.040
You have to admit...

31:19.049 --> 31:21.061
we're connected.

31:22.660 --> 31:24.233
Not by love.

31:24.360 --> 31:26.751
Ahh. Well, then...

31:27.429 --> 31:31.729
you have yet to truly reflect.

31:33.119 --> 31:38.379
So tell me, hmm,
on this-- this cozy night of--

31:38.517 --> 31:39.433
night of truths,

31:39.543 --> 31:42.143
when did you realize
that I was, uh,

31:42.319 --> 31:44.104
I was the killer?

31:45.200 --> 31:47.080
I started following you.

31:47.190 --> 31:51.196
No, Ryan.
You didn't follow me.

31:51.810 --> 31:56.194
No. You followed Claire.

31:59.450 --> 32:03.312
I followed her to see if
she would lead me to you.

32:05.760 --> 32:09.043
And then you fell
in love with her.

32:11.530 --> 32:13.138
Yeah.

32:19.828 --> 32:21.542
That will make this

32:22.133 --> 32:24.426
all the easier to do.

32:24.937 --> 32:25.851
Let's begin.

32:25.950 --> 32:27.398
- Aah! No!
- Wait! Don't! Don't!

32:27.503 --> 32:30.160
Joe, don't. It's
too predictable.

32:30.274 --> 32:31.280
You got to kill me instead.

32:31.408 --> 32:33.344
That's-- that's not
the ending, Ryan.

32:33.459 --> 32:35.698
No, Joe!
Please, please, Joe.

32:35.808 --> 32:37.850
Shall we start with her eyes?

32:37.956 --> 32:39.179
No. Joe, stop.
Listen!

32:39.286 --> 32:40.350
You got to kill me.

32:40.469 --> 32:41.965
No one's gonna see it coming.

32:44.085 --> 32:45.070
It's the best ending.

32:45.154 --> 32:46.868
I'm the hero.
You can let her go,

32:46.988 --> 32:48.275
but I have got to die.

32:48.375 --> 32:49.716
No one is gonna expect that!

32:49.806 --> 32:52.227
Claire must die, Ryan,

32:52.349 --> 32:54.216
to honor your death curse

32:54.322 --> 32:56.939
because it is by far

32:57.027 --> 32:59.722
the most interesting thing
about you!

32:59.829 --> 33:01.455
It's not gonna work, Joe.

33:01.543 --> 33:03.216
It's overkill.

33:03.309 --> 33:05.596
You're gonna destroy the story.

33:05.707 --> 33:07.486
No one's gonna read that.

33:07.565 --> 33:08.457
It reeks.

33:08.545 --> 33:09.945
You don't even know
good writing.

33:10.089 --> 33:11.464
That's why you're
a teacher, right?

33:11.556 --> 33:14.409
Those that can do, and
those that can't teach.

33:17.922 --> 33:19.986
Listen to you,

33:20.669 --> 33:24.022
trying to get
under my skin. Heh.

33:25.880 --> 33:27.861
Yeah. It's not hard.

33:28.126 --> 33:30.108
See, I know all
the trigger words--

33:31.169 --> 33:36.566
- second-rate, no-talent, wannabe...
- Yeah.

33:36.711 --> 33:40.211
Pretentious, overwrought, flop.

33:44.174 --> 33:46.949
I'm so bored with you.

33:47.453 --> 33:51.287
I'm so bored with you
and Edgar Allan Poe.

33:53.421 --> 33:58.409
What a trumped up piece
of nothing talent he was.

33:58.522 --> 33:59.911
Loser morphine addict

34:00.008 --> 34:02.215
just as pathetic as you.

34:02.483 --> 34:03.986
Aah! Aah!

34:06.688 --> 34:08.007
Go!

34:13.512 --> 34:14.993
- You all right?
- Yes.

34:15.136 --> 34:16.248
Kill him.

34:16.349 --> 34:17.801
Go kill him!

36:08.446 --> 36:09.682
Ryan!

36:57.036 --> 36:58.226
ERT's combing the area.

36:58.344 --> 36:59.487
We got dive teams in the water.

36:59.579 --> 37:00.615
They found partial remains.

37:00.701 --> 37:02.394
Claire mentioned a guy
Neil Meyer.

37:02.504 --> 37:03.923
I want confirmation
that's Joe's body

37:04.024 --> 37:04.962
they're finding.

37:05.061 --> 37:07.416
Well, we won't know until
we run official tests.

37:07.518 --> 37:09.122
Coroner confirmed
a dental match.

37:09.239 --> 37:11.418
Anybody contact
Parker's family yet?

37:11.663 --> 37:13.765
Quantico reached out
to her sister.

37:13.862 --> 37:15.797
I was gonna call once
we got finished up here.

37:15.886 --> 37:17.487
What about the rest
of the followers?

37:17.576 --> 37:19.772
Well, we got 7 total
in custody.

37:21.994 --> 37:24.548
Is he dead?
Did they find the body?

37:24.643 --> 37:26.285
Yeah. What's
left of him.

37:26.370 --> 37:28.199
You're sure. You have
to be sure it's him.

37:28.300 --> 37:29.095
Are you sure?

37:29.206 --> 37:31.316
We'll have official
confirmation soon.

37:32.293 --> 37:34.580
Claire, I have a call for you.

37:34.814 --> 37:36.244
I think you'll want to take it.

37:36.693 --> 37:38.088
Hello?

37:42.492 --> 37:46.225
Hi, Joey.
Hi. It's mommy.

37:46.410 --> 37:49.190
Joey's in DC. The debriefing
will start tomorrow.

37:49.291 --> 37:50.304
I'm gonna take her
back to my place,

37:50.404 --> 37:51.538
and we'll fly down first thing.

37:51.637 --> 37:52.981
I'll send some men with you.

38:04.865 --> 38:06.575
You okay?

38:08.445 --> 38:09.899
No.

38:22.300 --> 38:23.838
Just like the main character

38:23.968 --> 38:26.030
in this novel "The Gothic Sea,"

38:26.176 --> 38:29.505
serial killer Joe Carroll's
life came to an end

38:29.638 --> 38:32.418
early this morning when he was
burned to death in a fire...

38:32.514 --> 38:33.849
Okay. Thanks.

38:34.045 --> 38:35.381
...escape the FBI.

38:35.479 --> 38:37.167
Sources within the Bureau
tell us...

38:37.302 --> 38:38.443
Is it true?

38:38.548 --> 38:41.888
Dental records match,
early DNA.

38:42.344 --> 38:43.643
He's dead.

38:46.571 --> 38:48.275
- Oh. Ahh.
- You okay?

38:48.413 --> 38:51.341
Yeah. I'm just--
I'm a little sore.

38:52.904 --> 38:54.333
I'm fine.

39:15.555 --> 39:16.646
You hungry?

39:16.746 --> 39:19.381
Yeah, I'm starving.
Do you-- do you have food?

39:19.504 --> 39:20.490
- No.
- No.

39:21.091 --> 39:23.158
All right.
I'll get cleaned up.

39:23.779 --> 39:27.698
...Captured Carroll
on the Winslow University campus

39:27.821 --> 39:29.383
10 years ago.

39:29.633 --> 39:32.035
Once again, for those of you
just tuning in,

39:32.137 --> 39:36.321
we have confirmed
that Joe Carroll is dead.

39:36.414 --> 39:38.918
We know that many of Carroll's
followers have been exposed,

39:39.033 --> 39:42.567
leaving his cult of killers
all but dismantled.

39:42.658 --> 39:44.588
These recent developments
leave us with the hope

39:44.680 --> 39:49.049
that Joe Carroll's terror
has finally come to an end.

39:49.181 --> 39:51.450
We will continue to bring you
more on this story

39:51.585 --> 39:53.961
as information
becomes available.

40:17.681 --> 40:20.063
We intercepted this downstairs.

40:20.689 --> 40:22.069
What do I owe you?

40:22.245 --> 40:23.530
It's on us.

40:24.339 --> 40:25.546
Thanks, man.

41:12.837 --> 41:15.143
Unh! Unh!

41:17.938 --> 41:20.553
You were always
my chapter, Ryan.

41:20.645 --> 41:23.753
Joe promised me
I would be the one.

41:28.489 --> 41:30.583
Okay.
I smell food.

41:31.376 --> 41:32.259
Claire!

41:32.371 --> 41:34.676
Ryan! No, no!

41:35.209 --> 41:36.343
No!

41:36.740 --> 41:38.099
Ohh!

41:38.181 --> 41:40.165
No, no!

